-- Citigroup Hires Four for European Equity-Derivatives Trading, Memo Says
-- Alexis Xydias
-- 2010-07-07T15:19:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/citigroup-hires-four-for-european-equity-derivatives-trading-memo-says.html

          
          
             Citigroup Inc. has hired four
directors for its equity derivatives trading division in Europe,
according to an internal memo obtained by Bloomberg News.  
 Chiehmi Chan was appointed managing director and head of
European equity derivatives index trading, while Utz
Oberhansberg will join as managing director in the team, the
memo said. Iain Clamp joins as director in the team. All will be
based in London.  
 Chan will report to Antonin Jullier and Ronan Connolly,
deputy heads of trading for Europe, Middle East and Africa
equities.  
 The U.S. bank also hired Enrico Lais as director on the
single-stock derivatives trading desk, the information said.  
          
          


  


        